[5] Dysentery - Myanmar (Mandalay)
Date: Wed, 8 Sep 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Democratic Voice of Burma [edited]
<http://english.dvb.no/news.php?id=3012>

Dysentery outbreak in Mandalay
------------------------------
There has been a serious outbreak of dysentery at Mandalay in the
central part of the country. Several people, mainly school children,
have died as the result of the outbreak. According to a local
resident, the outbreak has lasted nearly a week.
Both public and private hospitals have been filled with patients, and
some have to camp outside the hospitals on bamboo mats due to lack of
beds. The outbreak is due to the chemicals and fertilizers used to
make fruits and vegetables more productive.
The local authorities are shutting down all fruit and vegetable
stores and warning people on loudspeakers not to eat ripened fruits
and vegetables.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[If this outbreak is indeed due to shigellosis, it is likely that it is not
the chemicals or fertilizers causing it, unless the fertilizers are of human
origin. - Mod.LL]
[Alternatively, the journalist is using the word "dysentery" in its broad
sense to mean bloody diarrhea, independent of cause, in which case this could
be an episode of chemical poisoning. More details would be welcome. - Mod.JW]
