[6] Dysentery - Russia (Perm)
Date: Fri, 3 Sep 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Regions.Ru News information agency [translated by Mod.NR; edited]
<http://www.regions.ru/printnewsarticle/news/id/1622441.html>

An outbreak of dysentery in Perm
--------------------------------
In Perm, 89 people from various parts of the region, including 2
children, have developed dysentery.
According to the sanitary surveillance center, the infections were
caused by eating salads bought in local shops 27-30 Aug 2004.
Disease and positive tests for _Shigella sonnei_ were reported among
the staff of the shops.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Perm is just west of the Ural mountains, in European Russia, approx. 58N
58E. - Mod.JW]
